summary: I can’t win this war without these people. But the potential cost feels… heavy. Watching your friends–who are already soldiers...
text: I can’t win this war without these people. But the potential cost feels… heavy. Watching your friends–who are already soldiers of a sort–train for war is one thing. Watching them train civilians is quite another. But our only way out is through. And it’s freedom for all of us or none of us. So while I count the costs… I’ll ask my army to consider something more inspiring. A favourite of [Sun] Tzu’s, perhaps… ‘Can you imagine what I would do if I could do all I can?’

summary: I love that scene in Endgame where Clint passed the Nano Gauntlet to T’challa, then Peter, then Carol. It’s like symbolically...
body:
The Next Big Three

I love that scene in Endgame where Clint passed the Nano Gauntlet to T’challa, then Peter, then Carol. It’s like symbolically passing the torch to the next big three. Others think it isn’t so but come to think of it, it makes sense. Here’s why:

The Resilient

Steve is well known by the line “I can do this all day” meaning he can fight as long as there are people that needed protection or as long as a battle rages on as seen at that time he faced Thanos’ army alone. Captain Marvel, through her movie, always gets up despite the people around her pushing her down, belittling her or simply not letting her use her full potential. Both of them never stay down.

Why Carol and not Sam? Kevin Feige already said Captain Marvel is the next face of the MCU. The thing is, I don’t think she’ll be the only face of the MCU in the future.

The Noble

Nobility doesn’t just equate to being born a royal. A person with noble character is one that is generous, honorable and one with integrity. Sure, both of them were from a line of royals but their characters also embody mercy and kindness; characters of a good king. The only difference is that T’challa accepted the throne and still become a good man. He learned to balance being a king and still being true to himself. Thor needs a bit of soul searching to be his true self.

The Heart

Tony and Peter are similar: they’re both self-sacrificing idiots (I know too soon, but it’s true). Both have hearts big enough to love and shoulders strong enough to carry the world. Both will not stop until the people they love stays protected. Despite the tragedies in their lives, they still have the heart to love.

Others are hesitant to think that Peter could be one of the next big three because of the deal with Sony; saying that Sony can just pull Spidey out of the MCU after Tom Holland’s contract is over but business-wise, that’s stupid. Sony can get more profits while doling out way less money. They have the advantage in keeping Spidey in the MCU. So, the best they can do is extend their deal with Marvel. Then again, what do I know. This is just a theory and I’ve been wrong before. *shrug*
